      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Treatment of <i>trans</i>-2-chlorocyclohexanol with NaOH yields 1,2-epoxycyclohexane, but reaction of the cis isomer under the same conditions yields cyclohexanone. Propose mechanisms for both reactions, and explain why the different results are obtained.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcUlYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--413617dc7c6e97366ffae125e5538f456b8b241a/OChem_18_EC_035.jpg\" alt=\"Reactions alter trans-2-chlorocyclohexanol to 1,2-epoxycyclohexane and cis-2-chlorocyclohexanol isomer to cyclohexanone, each utilizing sodium hydroxide and water.\">",
